---
alwaysApply: true
---

Always keep colors centralized in dedicated theme/config files and never hardcode colors directly inside UI components.
Use a global color system that can be reused across the entire project.
Support light/dark themes through centralized theme management whenever possible.
Keep typography, spacing, radius, shadows, and reusable design tokens in separate style files.
Localization & Translations
All translations must be stored in dedicated localization files.
Never hardcode user-facing text directly inside components or pages.
The project must support multi-language expansion from the beginning.
Use translation keys with clear naming conventions.
Keep translations organized by feature/module when appropriate.
UI & Accessibility
Ensure all text fields, labels, placeholders, buttons, and inputs have sufficient contrast against their backgrounds.
Avoid low-contrast text combinations that reduce readability.
Inputs must remain readable in all states (focused, disabled, error, success).
Respect accessibility best practices for colors and typography.
Code Quality
Reusable logic must be extracted into shared utilities, services, hooks, or helpers.
Avoid duplicated styles and repeated UI logic.
Maintain clean folder structure and naming consistency.
Prefer scalable and maintainable architecture over quick fixes.
Before Implementing Any Feature

Cursor must:

Analyze existing architecture and follow the current project structure.
Reuse existing theme, localization, and shared components whenever possible.
Avoid introducing hardcoded values unless absolutely necessary.
Ensure new code is production-ready, scalable, and maintainable.
